"Restrepo C., Walker L.R., Shiels A.B., Bussmann R., Claessens L., Fisch S., Lozano P., Negi G., Paolini L., Poveda G., Ramos-Scharrón C., Richter M., Velázquez E.","Landsliding and its multiscale influence on mountainscapes",2009,"BioScience","59","8",,"685","698",,,10.1525/bio.2009.59.8.10,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-70149100667&partnerID=40&md5=06901784856ff64d5c858942cbe65d96","Department of Biology, University of Puerto Rico, Río Piedras, San Juan, Puerto Rico; Universidad de Alcalá, Spain; Department of Botany, University of Hawai'i at Manoa, Honolulu, United States; William L.Brown Center for Plant Genetic Resources, Missouri Botanical Garden, St. Louis, United States; International Potato Center, Nairobi, Kenya; Land Dynamics Group, Wageningen University, Netherlands; Departamento de Biologia, Universidade de Taubaté, Brazil; Institute of Botany and Botanical Garden, Hohenheim University, Stuttgart, Germany; Department of Forest Ecology, Pant Institute of Himalayan Environment and Development, Uttarakland, India; Laboratorio de Investigaciones Ecológicas de Las Yungas, Yerba Buena, Tucumán, Argentina; Escuela de Geociencias y Del Ambiente, Universidad Nacional de Colombia I, Medellín, Colombia; Institut für Geographie, Friedrich-Alexander Universität, Erlangen, Nürnberg, Germany","Restrepo, C., Department of Biology, University of Puerto Rico, Río Piedras, San Juan, Puerto Rico; Walker, L.R., Universidad de Alcalá, Spain; Shiels, A.B., Department of Botany, University of Hawai'i at Manoa, Honolulu, United States; Bussmann, R., William L.Brown Center for Plant Genetic Resources, Missouri Botanical Garden, St. Louis, United States; Claessens, L., International Potato Center, Nairobi, Kenya, Land Dynamics Group, Wageningen University, Netherlands; Fisch, S., Departamento de Biologia, Universidade de Taubaté, Brazil; Lozano, P., Institute of Botany and Botanical Garden, Hohenheim University, Stuttgart, Germany; Negi, G., Department of Forest Ecology, Pant Institute of Himalayan Environment and Development, Uttarakland, India; Paolini, L., Laboratorio de Investigaciones Ecológicas de Las Yungas, Yerba Buena, Tucumán, Argentina; Poveda, G., Escuela de Geociencias y Del Ambiente, Universidad Nacional de Colombia I, Medellín, Colombia; Ramos-Scharrón, C., Department of Biology, University of Puerto Rico, Río Piedras, San Juan, Puerto Rico; Richter, M., Universidad de Alcalá, Spain, Institut für Geographie, Friedrich-Alexander Universität, Erlangen, Nürnberg, Germany; Velázquez, E., Universidad de Alcalá, Spain","Landsliding is a complex process that modifies mountainscapes worldwide. Its severe and sometimes long-lasting negative effects contrast with the less-documented positive effects on ecosystems, raising numerous questions about the dual role of landsliding the feedbacks between biotic and geomorphic processes, and, ultimately, the ecological and evolutionary responses of organisms. We present a conceptual model in which feedbacks between biotic and geomorphic processes, landslides, and ecosystem attributes are hypothesized to drive the dynamics of mountain ecosystems at multiple scales. This model is used to integrate and synthesize a rich, but fragmented, body of literature generated in different disciplines, and to highlight the need for profitable collaborations between biologists and geoscientists. Such efforts should help identify attributes that contribute to the resilience of mountain ecosystems, and also should help in conservation, restoration, and hazard assessment. Given the sensitivity of mountains to land-use and global climate change, these endeavors are both relevant and timely. © 2009 by American Institute of Biological Sciences. All rights reserved.","Biotic and geomorphic processes; Conservation; Landslides; Mountains",,,,,,,"Bak, P., Tang, C., Wiesenfeld, K., Self-organized criticality (1988) Physical Review A, 38, pp. 364-374; Bastos-Neto, A.T., Stv, F., Comunidade de palmeira